Package eu.profinit.manta.connector.erstudio.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CompositeDataObject
    Depending on its AbstractionLayer this is a contract of a TableAbstractionLayer.PHYSICAL or of an EntityAbstractionLayer.LOGICAL.
    DataModel
    Interface for read only access to a DataModel, that is a set of CompositeDataObjects.
    DataObject
    An interface for accessing any data object that is modeled in some DataModel.
    ErStudioFile
    ER/Studio's .DM1 file loaded into data structure with no processing besides of loading its plain structure.
    ErStudioFileModel
    Interface allowing read-only access to a completely loaded structure from one .DM1 file.
    ErStudioSolution
    An ErStudioSolution interface provides an access to a Logical and set of Physical models and their underlying DataObjects.
    Layered
    An object that can tell on what AbstractionLayer it is modeled.
    LogicalDataModel
    Interface providing access to a database model created with higher level of abstraction of its objects.
    Mappable<T extends DataObject>
    Interface for getting information about mappings of objects that can be mapped to zero or more DataObjects.
    Owner
    Container of composite objects.
    PhysicalDataModel
    Representation of database technology specific model.
    Platform
    Database platform.
    SimpleDataObject
    Depending on its AbstractionLayer this is a contract of a ColumnAbstractionLayer.PHYSICAL or of an AttributeAbstractionLayer.LOGICAL.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AbstractionLayer
    Possible levels of abstraction on which objects can be modeled in ER/Studio
    ConnectionType
    Types of database management systems supported by ER/Studio.
